values: i have been hurt to many times, by to many people that i love. but this one is the worst cause i do know we are just on a break but everytime i see her or think of her or think about this stupid break i cry, like alot. this whole thing just makes me think i should get up and leave. i dont know if its the right decision or the wrong. but if i were i would not know if i would get hurt wherever i go. i probably would cause i guess im just that easy to hurt. i love her more and more every day, and i get more and more depressed when im not with her. i would do anything for her, she is my love, my honey bee, my kelly. no matter what happened between us i didnt care, as long as we stayed together. she did try breaking up with me once before and i wouldnt let her. i dont see any other girl attractive anymore, she is the one and only person i love, she makes me want to live. but now that all might be gone, cause she might be gone,found someone new. or just got plane old bored with me. she told me that i was always a wonderful boyfriend, an amazing friend, and a great person. but it makes me think if i am all those why does she not want to be with me.

life is full of  dating, falling in love, friends, family, and pain. ofcourse there is alot of other stuff but this stuff is what i expecially want to talk about right now. the reason im talking about is because well i havent been in here for a very long time, and its what has been on my mind for a couple of days. so im just gonna go off starting in 3..........2............1.........


just in high school i have dated my fair share of people i have loved some of them and i treated most of them horribly. to all those people that i treated horribly i am sorry, if i could go back i would change it. then there were some that treated me like shit too. but its ok because of my dating history it has given me the knowledge of not being a horrible bf, but i do have to say this it has been really hard to find someone who loves me for who i am, not for who they want me to become. 

my friends mean the world to me, they are the reason im still here. i would be lost if i didnt have them, expecially john. john is my best friend, he is my brother, i would take a bullet for him.i expecially have to thank adriana for showing me the most wonderful person ever(mandi). but i have alot of great friends, they have helped me through thick and thin.

well my family is just really a bunch of fucked up people whho like to drink. i cant really think of much to say about them though.

everyone gets hurt in there life, from love to actually hruting them selves. everyone will eventually get over that pain, or make it seem that way. if you get hurt from love yes it will hurt for a while, and it will always hurt inside.but thats life and there really isnt much you can do about that.

this is to everyone in the world if you cnat accept me for who i am then there is no place for you in my life.

i want everyone to remeber this.....relationships make the world go around, love just makes it a safer place.

Love is like 30 Knives,
Driving into your heart.
Sacrificing everything,
To be with her.
Seconds, minutes, hours,
Buying everything she wants.
Soon all you have is petty cash.
See her flirting with someone else.
Then you feel love sick, Heartbroken.
No reason to live,
Want to be murdered, be slaughtered,
maybe beheaded.
No point to love ever again.


a poem i wrote in the 7th grade

The Value of Drink
Sometimes when I reflect back on all the wine I drink
I feel shame Then I look into the glass and think
about the workers in the vineyards and all of their hopes
and dreams . If I didn't drink this wine, they might be out
of work and their dreams would be shattered.
Then I say to myself, "It is better that I drink this wine and let their
dreams come true than be selfish and worry about my liver."
~ Jack Handy

And saving the best for last, as explained by Cliff Clavin, of Cheers
One afternoon at Cheers, Cliff Clavin was explaining the Buffalo Theory
to his buddy Norm.
Here's how it went:

"Well ya see, Norm, it's like this... A herd of buffalo can only move as
fast as the slowest buffalo. And when the herd is hunted, it is the slowest
and weakest ones at the back that are killed first. This natural selection
is good for the herd as a whole, because the general speed and health of
the whole group keeps improving by the regular killing of the weakest
members.
In much the same way, the human brain can only operate as fast as the
slowest brain cells. Excessive intake of alcohol, as we know, kills brain
cells. But naturally, it attacks the slowest and weakest brain cells first.
In this way, regular consumption of beer eliminates the weaker brain
cells, making the brain a faster and more efficient machine. That's why you
always feel smarter after a few beers."
